{
  "doc_id": "34909",
  "text": "Differentiation of benign mediastinal tumors from malignancies is essential to determining therapeutic options and assessing the prognosis. Several studies have denoted that mediastinal tumors have characteristic CT and MRI findings [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] . Nonetheless, modalities such as CT or MRI could not distinguish between benign and malignant tumors accurately [CITATION_5] [CITATION_6] [CITATION_7] [CITATION_8] [CITATION_9] .",
